cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.LG

The paper discusses privacy-enhancing technologies used for testing, storing, and sharing genomic data, which involves sensitive personal information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the challenges of storing and managing large amounts of data, which suggests cs.DB (Databases) as a possible category. The paper also touches on ethical and legal issues related to genomic data, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper relies on a structured methodology to analyze the current knowledge, which could be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
